namedLocations.description: In online marketing a landing page, sometimes known as a "lead capture page" or a "lander", is a single web page that appears in response to clicking on a search engine optimized search result or an online advertisement. The landing page will usually display directed sales copy that is a logical extension of the advertisement, search result or link. Landing pages are often linked to from social media, email campaigns or search engine marketing campaigns in order to enhance the effectiveness of the advertisements. The general goal of a landing page is to convert site visitors into sales or leads. By analyzing activity generated by the linked URL, marketers can use click-through rates and conversion rate to determine the success of an advertisement.

transcript.text: Hello welcome to on print shop.
In this video we will learn corporate wise configuration settings.
Previously we had common setting for configuration under site setting in Super admin.
But now we have collected all corporate related configuration settings and then added a new tab under Corporate action menu.
This feature will be available through given instruction.
First of all select Corporate section from Corporate Management module in Admin.
Then click on the Action button for Corporate.
Select Settings from the menu.
Here we have corporate specific configuration settings.
Let's take some examples.
You see the send mail functionality is activated for public store.
But for specific corporate we don't want to display send mail functionality.
So we select corporate specific in setting type and then select No.
Now click on the save button and refresh the page on the front store.
We will see that option is disappeared.
Now let's see another example.
Here you see for the public store number of products to be displayed on homepage is 12 and number of products to be displayed in each row on homepage is 3 and same we can see on front store.
Let's say now you want to display 8 product on homepage and four product in each row for a specific corporate without affecting public store.
Then from the admin we need to select corporate specific in the setting type and enter 8:00 and 4:00 as we want.
Click on the save button to save the changes for corporate.
Refresh the page on front store to see the changes.
Here you see three products are showing in a row for the public store, but four products are showing in a row for the corporate store.
Thank you for watching this video.
For more help, please send us an e-mail at support at on printshop.com.
